                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Outer Mongolia/94: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-02T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 2, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 2—10:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. I am informed by spokesman of the Foreign Office that press reports of
                    declaration of autonomy by Teh Wang are not correct and that Teh Wang has
                    telegraphed assurances to this effect.</p>
                <p>To the Department and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
